<subSubSection id="1B3988C741AFF73A07D42D89D285517A" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="FBB8E58D24E53A411FB8CF548A3A915E" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName id="2010FE7848F26A133EBE254B0041206F" authorityName="Bellot &amp; Renner" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="holtzii" status="nom. inval.">Pilostyles holtzii</taxonomicName>
Engler, Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 46: 293. 1912 = 
<taxonomicName id="31DF768DDC54C4D94D5BAB7292750BC8" authorityName="Bellot &amp; Renner" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Berlinianche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="holtzii" status="nom. inval.">
<emphasis id="4078BA2622BD0A0A79B415B1D43FCB03" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinianche holtzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Engl.) Vattimo-Gil, not validly published. Type: Tanzania, Kilimatinde, July 1907, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName id="4DAAE770537058C47E2AD27EFBBDA590" authorityName="Bellot &amp; Renner" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Berlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="eminii" status="nom. inval.">
<emphasis id="4706FD92FAB1A1EE901825E5AA620AFF" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinia eminii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Taub., 
<emphasis id="FA9DA7FB4BB32F41B062740F050860A9" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">W. Holtz 1422</emphasis>
(B, destroyed during World War II), 
<emphasis id="44155AFF7FBC9983FDBA0689097C4BF6" bold="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">syn. nov.</emphasis>
(based on the protologue).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1D94E350A0FB82A3405EE171D61A5994" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="syntypes">
<paragraph id="452017538E8EBF5BB6F1965D2810A049" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Syntypes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="55C085026A81ACA3432C6C3218CD51B7" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Angola, Huila, 12 May 1860, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName id="58E0C17E3F164D3D7A968001A14F4FA1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Berlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis id="1F6CCEBFB4426594171B030E5E6CEB82" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinia paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Benth. = 
<taxonomicName id="4204EE5C1920F323BDA30CBE6D5099C0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Pseudoberlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis id="1C0B0C043188E23A32C09AFFA216FD61" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Pseudoberlinia paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Benth.) P.A.Duvign., 
<emphasis id="9FC44FB583D254370437255E64855327" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">F. M. J. Welwitsch 529, 529b</emphasis>
(C, G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58FF683E7EFF27DC5D6DC80E767D71C1" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="note">
<paragraph id="FAED93D1D1EDA4BEBD02A3137AE992D8" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4DAF162C81405BFB1403EE047D0A303" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Tepals pink to brown, in 3 to 4 whorls each with 3-6 tepals. Male flowers with 1 or 2 ring(s) of ca. 15 pollen sacs, stamen filaments free from the central column (Fig. 6F), hair cushion at the basis of the inner tepals (
<bibRefCitation id="10BE2A95E5B1F90462EB6A23C155A819" author="Blarer, A" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" refId="B4" refString="Blarer, A, Nickrent, DL, Endress, PK, 2004. Comparative floral structure and systematics in Apodanthaceae (Rafflesiales). Plant Systematics and Evolution 245: 119-142. doi 10.1007/s00606-003-0090-2." title="Comparative floral structure and systematics in Apodanthaceae (Rafflesiales). Plant Systematics and Evolution 245: 119 - 142. doi 10.1007 / s 00606 - 003 - 0090 - 2" year="2004">Blarer et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Growing in branches of 
<taxonomicName id="BF262D7B43E4515B31EA20871A470FA2" authorityName="Pellegrin" authorityYear="1943" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Julbernardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="624B1DEFEF6574B622FB9BF1D6D0D11C" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Julbernardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3031F170333852947BC75B78AB9F1E3C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Brachystegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7733A2EAA4F26ADD54B2483661AFB36F" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Brachystegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, maybe also on 
<taxonomicName id="7DE13542C36D76B8FE89E83079EE5061" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Berlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BC189CF08EA4CDF4389BCA48534AAAE1" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="519AFF38259D221EEAA3031AC337EF60" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Westia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="14B12392E9E2D2A1343489B96E135E94" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Westia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="68085EECE6A359C711E3027ABA039921" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Pseudoberlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1064BE72FECDF68CA7BB5B62BEDC4CC2" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Pseudoberlinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in Zimbabwe, Zambia, Tanzania, Angola and Malawi (
<figureCitation id="CBDA910C161DF24972DCFBA718867CA2" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Geographic distribution of Apodanthaceae based on label information from 785 herbarium collections." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10621" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="228E884CDCB11815F82E398A81EA7779" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Phylogenetic relationships among the hosts of Apodanthaceae (legume relationships from Wojciechowski et al. 2006) and among the species of Apodanthaceae (from Bellot and Renner in review). Identical colors link parasite species and their host (s) and are also used in Figure 2. Dashed lines represent associations with rarely reported hosts; hosts in bold are the most common ones." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10622" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
